  "texts": [
    "Table 4 provides the evidence profile for the outcomes examined in this study.",
    "The evidence quality was 'low' for the effectiveness of the technique and 'moderate' for the ease of clinical applicability.",
    "The majority of the included studies [12, 14, 27-31, 9, 32, 36, 37, 39-49, 51-53] constructed a cephalometric MSP, while eight studies computed a morphometric MSP [3, 17, 21-24, 34, 38] for the assessment of asymmetry (Table 3).",
    "In addition, five studies employed both cephalometric and morphometric MSP construction methods [4, 15, 25, 35, 50], while four studies assessed asymmetry using a symmetry plane [1, 26, 9, 33].",
    "For the cephalometric MSP construction, N-S was the most consistently used landmark combination [12, 28, 35, 39, 40, 43, 47, 48]."
  ],
